'''Kameyama Shrine''' (亀山神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Kure|ja|呉市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Hiroshima Prefecture|ja|広島県|12=draft}}. The former {{ill|Modern shrine Ranking system|ja|近代Rank制度|12=draft}} classification was a {{ill|Prefectural shrine|ja|県社|12=draft}}, and it is currently a {{ill|Beppyo shrine|ja|別表神社|12=draft}} under the {{ill|Association of Shinto Shrines|ja|神社本庁|12=draft}}. It is revered as the general {{ill|Ujigami|ja|氏神|12=draft}} of the old Kure city area.

== Deities ==
The shrine enshrines the {{ill|Hachiman|ja|八幡神|12=draft}}, namely Hondawakeno Mikoto ({{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|応神天皇|12=draft}}), Oshihomimi no Mikoto ({{ill|Emperor Chūai|ja|仲哀天皇|12=draft}}), and Okitsuhime no Mikoto ({{ill|Empress Jingū|ja|神功皇后|12=draft}}).
<gallery>
File:亀山神社 二の鳥居.jpg|二の鳥居
</gallery>

== History ==
The shrine traces its origins to the {{ill|Hachiman Shrine|ja|八幡神社|12=draft}} that was initially enshrined in {{ill|Usa Shrine|ja|宇佐神宮|12=draft}} in {{ill|Buzen Province|ja|豊前国|12=draft}}. It is said that the deity was relocated through {{ill|Himeshima|ja|姫島|12=draft}} in {{ill|Bungo Province|ja|豊後国|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Togihara|ja|栃原|12=draft}} in {{ill|Aki Province|ja|安芸国|12=draft}}, before finally being enshrined at Kameyama (Irifuneyama) in Miyahara Village on August 15, Taihō 3 (703). The shrine has been known by various names, including Ōjō-no-miya, Ōyabe Hime Shrine, Ōtake Hime Shrine, Hime Shima Shrine, and Suzune-no-miya, but it was commonly referred to as "Hachiman-sama." In {{ill|Meiji 19|ja|明治19th year|12=draft}} (1886), the shrine was relocated to its current location to facilitate the establishment of the Kure Naval District.

The shrine was elevated to the Rank of prefectural shrine in {{ill|Shōwa 16|ja|昭和16th year|12=draft}} (1941), and in {{ill|Shōwa 32|ja|昭和32nd year|12=draft}} (1957), it was designated as a {{ill|Beppyo shrine|ja|別表神社|12=draft}}.

== See Also ==
* {{ill|Irifuneyama Park|ja|入船山公園|12=draft}}

== External Links ==
* [http://www.kameyama-jinja.com Kameyama Shrine] (Official website)
* [http://www.facebook.com/Kameyama.Jinja Kameyama Shrine Facebook] (Official)

